question
Write a function isValid that checks if the value argument contains NaN.

If the argument is NaN, return the string "Value is not a number".

Otherwise, return the string "Value is valid".

Use the Number.isNaN (value) method in your solution

solution:

function isValid(value){
  if(Number.isNaN(value)) return "Value is not a number";
    else 
  return "Value is valid";
}
